items.name: Nemona (Pokemon) LoRA
items.description:
Believe it or not, she wants to battle again...

General Info

This LoRA has been trained using the Anything v4.5 model. It does a great job at generating characters that look a lot like Nemona from Pokemon Scarlet and Violet. The LoRA even has some variation when it comes to the style and pose she is displayed in and the clothes she wears. The model seems to also have quite some nsfw capabilities but they have not been tested.

Usage

The model has been trained using Kohya so you probably want to use it in the same way as you use other Kohya models. If you are Using A1111's Webui you want to move the file into the models>Lora directory. It is very important to use the relevant trigger word so that you can get results that look close to mine or even better. I advise using a weight of 0.6-1.0 but you might even be able to go lower in some cases.

items.name: Dehya (Genshin Impact)
items.description:
LoRA

A LoRA for Dehya from Genshin Impact.

All sample images are generated with my custom merged model UmbraMix

Prompts

  • Positive prompts should have a minimum of details about the character. Even if dehya and dehya \(genshin impact\) are the main trigger word, when used by themselves alone may produce unwanted results.

  • Negative prompts should be as simple as possible such as (worst quality, low quality:1.4), (blurry:1.4).

  • All sample prompts are generate with a CLIP SKIP value of 2

Weights

I recommend using the fallowing weights:

  • Closest to the character : 0.85 ~ 1.0

  • When trying to add / change the character clothing/assets : 0.5~0.75

items.description:
Stalin Diffusion

IMPORTANT NOTES:

>This model is NOT meant to share or glorify any political view.

>Trigger word: "JosephStalin". Recommended weight: 0.6 and higher.

>Trained on mostly b&w pictures, in order to get good results appropriate prompting and model is required.

>The best results achieved with realistic models (tested with Realistic Vision).

>Probably the easiest way it to just use inpaint.

Prompting

>Highly recommended to add this to your prompt:

  • Positive: in color

  • Negative: ((cartoon)), (comics), black and white, (blurry), (noise), (outline glow), monochrome, grain, oversaturated, simple background

>Trained mostly on upper body pictures, might be hard to get full body.

>Interesting images can be created with low CFG scale.

>I suggest using 768x768 resolution.

How to make a similar model

I know this model is far from being great, but if someone wants to know the workflow, here you go:

1. Find good images and crop them. 2. Upscale x2~x4 (in my case mostly R-ESRGAN). 3. Remove noise using any graphic software. 4. Scale down 5. Train LoRa (using Google Colab, e.g. Kohya Trainer).

I mostly use b&w photos, so following steps 2,3,4 leads to significant increase of quality and reduction of image noise.

Trigger word: piying

Adding "piying ride a horse" triggers the classic action of a shadow puppet riding a horse. Adding "lingzi hat" triggers "lingzi," ÁøéÂ≠ê which refers to the long feathers on top of a shadow puppet's head. When the additional words do not work, try using parentheses to strengthen them, for example, "(((lingzi)))". Using tags such as "Beijing Opera" or "Beijing opera costume" may produce better results.

Trained on anythingV4.5, it adapts well to most anime-style and2-D models. However, there is also a probability of generating "inhuman things", and you need to try more suitable prompt words and draw more cards. I have not tried it on realistic models as it may produce a terrifying figure. If anyone has achieved any results, please share them with me.

It adapts well to other stylized and character Loras, but the strength ratio of the two needs to be adjusted to achieve the desired effect. When the weight of the character Lora is low and the weight of this Lora is high, it tends to produce shadow puppets with character features and color tones. When the weight of this Lora is low, it tends to produce flat, intricately patterned characters (or Aranara). You may use the lower weight as an oriental retro-style stylized Lora. Please experiment with the strength personally or refer to my sample pictures.

items.name: knollingcase-embeddings-sd-v1-5
items.description:
Originally posted to HuggingFace.

The embeddings in this repository were trained for the 512px Stable Diffusion v1.5 model. The embeddings should work on any model that uses SD v1.5 as a base.

For Stable Diffusion v2.x, see my KnollingCase embeddings for SD 2.0.

Knollingcase v1

The v1 embeddings were trained for 4000 iterations with a batch size of 4 and a text dropout of 10%, using Automatic1111's WebUI. A total of 147 training images with high quality captions were used.

Embeddings are provided for steps 1000, 2000, 3000, & 4000.

Usage

To use the embeddings, download and then rename the files to whatever trigger word you want to use. They were trained with kc16, but any trigger word should work.

The knollingcase style is considered to be a concept inside a sleek (sometimes scifi) display case with transparent walls, and a minimalistic background.

The images of people standing inside the case were made with using the embeddings on the F222 model.

items.name: Bulma Brief (Multiple older versions) - Dragon Ball Z and Super
items.description:
This LORA objective is to produce as many Bulma variations as possible from Z and Super. I was unable to tag for outfits due to how stupidly large it was already. Bulma is just extremely prolific appearance wise having multiple outfits and hairstyles at different points.

I had forgotten the horror of making the first version of this LORA. I guess that's how women feel when giving birth to their second kid. Anyway. The LOCON Version is already out so try both and compare if you want.

V2:

Works fine with:<lora:buruma_brief_olderV2:0.7>,buruma_brief_older, <Bulma version>

Like this: <lora:buruma_brief_olderV2:0.7>, buruma_brief_older, buruma_dbz_buu, standing, solo, large_breasts

The available Bulma versions in this LOCON are:

  • buruma_dbz_start: Weird 80s punkish hair (Works better in the LOCON version)

  • buruma_dbz_namek: necklenght with her hairband

  • buruma_dbz_garlic: longer asymmetric hair

  • buruma_dbz_cell: A little longer than Namek and without the hairband

  • buruma_dbz_futuretimeline: Long hair

  • buruma_dbz_afro: Afro

  • buruma_dbz_buu: bobcut hair

  • buruma_super_start: Bobcut and looks older

  • buruma_super_resurrectionfreezer: similar to start but not quite

I leave to you her clothing tagging. You should be able to get the tags summary inside the dataset so experiment with that.

V1:

Seems people wanted an older Bulma as it seems current LORAS are from her pre DBZ self.

You can see the different variants included in the XYZ graph.

I had ok-ish results in the .45 to .65 range. If you go too low you might be caught in the transition between the normal eye and Toriyama style eyes.

I had best results with: buruma_brief_older, <insert one of the other Bulmas triggers here>, large_breasts, blue_eyes, <lora:Buruma_Brief_older:.5>

Like this: buruma_brief_older, Buruma_Super_ResurrectionFreezer, large_breasts, blue_eyes, <lora:Buruma_Brief_older:.5>

The supported variations of bulma are:

  • Buruma_DBZ_Start

  • Buruma_DBZ_Namek

  • Buruma_DBZ_Buu

  • Buruma_DBZ_Cell

  • Buruma_DBZ_FutureTimeline

  • Buruma_Super_start

  • Buruma_Super_ResurrectionFreezer

  • don't use any of them for a mixed style

I added the tag summary inside the training data.

Creating this was annoying as hell, it came out overfit no matter what i did until i noticed that the noise(Saw a big honking watermark) wasn't from my training data. I cleaned it properly damn it!

Turns out the LORA was getting contaminated with the model's Bulma concept which is fugly and overtrained. This caused my LORA to be overfit from epoch 1.

Long story short after cleaning the dataset and tags and cooking it with different learning rates and coming up empty I found the watermark in the noise.

Finally "fixed" the issue by changing the triggers to the romanji spelling thus why they use Buruma. Also during one of the dataset shiftings ended up tagging everything by saga so you can more or less reliably make the LORA spit individual Bulmas from different story arcs.

Not my best work but one of the more annoying and time consuming, on the other hand it is flexible as hell.

It still seems a bit overfit but I am just a bit tired of it.

What's UmbraMix?

Usage

  • For even more epic results, consider using the Hires. fix and/or high sampling step (~40 to ~80) specially when generating high resolution images.

  • Experiment, experiment, experiment!

    • No model is perfect, you may need to experiment and generate multiple images in order to get what you're looking for

    • Using different VAEs to best suit your style is recommended!

    • Extensive usage of ControlNet is recommended!

License

  • Since the models provided here are merges between other models, every model version inherits the license from the respective models that made up the merge

  • LoRA weight 0.7 ~ 0.8

    • Hair ornament (not necessary for new year costume)

      • hair ribbon, hair ornament, fingerless gloves, yellow gloves, japanese clothes, long sleeves, wide sleeves, detached sleeves, bare shoulders, clothing cutout, cleavage cutout, kouhaku nawa, brown skirt, pleated skirt, zettai ryouiki, black thighhighs, sandals, red footwear

    • New year :

      • official alternate costume, braid, fur collar, ear ornament, hair ornament, detached collar, bare shoulders, detached sleeves, strapless dress, wide sleeves, frilled sleeves, ribbon trim, feathers, white dress, thigh strap, thighhighs, tabi, white footwear, platform footwear, sandals

    • Aged down (animation) :

      • aged down, ponytail, hair ribbon, hair ornament, long sleeves, white shirt, track jacket, black jacket, open clothes, open jacket, food print, yellow shorts, black footwear, sneakers

    • Casual :

      • casual, hair ribbon, hair ornament, long sleeves, white sleeves, hoodie, hood down, hooded jacket, blue jacket, black shirt, yellow shorts, short shorts, black thighhighs, sneakers, shoes, red footwear

    • Tracen summer uniform :

      • tracen school uniform, summer uniform, serafuku, puffy short sleeves, bowtie, horseshoe ornament, sailor collar, sailor shirt, frills, white skirt, purple shirt, miniskirt, zettai ryouiki, white thighhighs, brown footwear, shoes

Use a model derived from or mixed with animefull model.

  • Settings

    • Stable Diffusion WebUI by Automatic1111

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • I recommend kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • Use Hires.fix to get higher quality image

      • Upscaler

        • Latent, Latent (nearest-exact), Latent (bicubic antialiased) or other Latent series.

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss.

    • LyCORIS by KohakuBlueleaf

    • Thank you all a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned model

  • 204 images consist of

    • => 1 epoch = 1840 images

  • replaced character feature tags with kitasan black (umamusume)

    • Eye

      • red eyes, brown eyes, orange eyes, yellow eyes,

    • Unnecessary

      • simple background, shimenawa, ear ribbon

  • I think these tags are

    • the essentials of Kitasan Black

    • or unnecessary for training because of duplication.

    • kitasan black \(umamusume\) contains above tags.

  • resolution : 768x768 with aspect ratio bucketing.

  • other training settings is included in training_data.zip or metadata in LoRA file.

And, special thanks to my best friend. DH.

Translate with DeepL:

After three months of testing back and forth, we finally have a milestone result.

Change to use LyCORIS for training to retain more details of clothing, this version of model needs to be loaded using a1111-sd-webui-lycoris plugin.

To the data set to add some new material, optimize the tagging method, now can be better separated from the features of several parts, the main tag is still nahida \(genshin impact\), mainly responsible for the head in addition to headdress and pupils other than the generation of features, four-leaf print pupils tag is cross-shaped pupils, but the current effect is not ideal. If you want to use the original clothing, you can add the following tags as needed: in-game dress, hair ornament, bloomers, stirrup legwear, bracelet, cape, want to change the reference legend with other tag.

Recommended unet weight 0.4~1.0, low weight may need to manually add ears, hairstyle tags pointy ears, multicolored hair, gradient hair, white hair, green hair to maintain character features.

If you feel that the picture is a little dirty, we recommend using ClearVAE to improve the quality.

V2.0 Update

I learned a lot in this month, and my graphic card also suffered a lot :P, till now I can publish a better version for this model

For this version, recommend weight is 0.45~0.7, only one trigger word nahida \(genshin impact\) is needed, but has better restoration of characteristic

My suggestion is use lower weight for model, and higher weight for trigger word, so you can easily change her suit

All known problems in previous version are solved

The next version will be a LyCORIS model, please stay tuned!

Any suggestions are welcome!

V1.0 Release

Genshin Impact Nahida LoRA, training with base model final-prune[925997e9].

Recommend weight 0.45~0.8. around 0.7 is a sweet spot for customize and keep characteristic.

Models used for examples:

  • Cetus-Mix

  • MeinaMix

  • AOAOKO [PVC Style Model] with VAE Counterfeit-V2.5

Use tags braid, sidelocks, side ponytail, multicolored hair, white hair, green hair, gradient hair to fix hair style.

Use tag bracelet to generate a in-game style bracelet (working better in higher weight).

Use tag white bloomer to add in-game style bloomer for charater.

Known problem:

  • Lower weight may cause a little incorrect on the green part of the hair color.

  • Sometimes a unexpected crown would appear on Nahida's head (mostly in higher weight).

Any suggestions are welcome!

items.name: Product Design (minimalism-eddiemauro)
items.description:
Before to use

  • You have to know how works Stable Diffusion. I recommend using Automatic1111 like an interface to launch the model.

  • This is a model trained on SD 1.5 model, so you have to consider that it is not perfect. I had to make so much testing before to arrive to a stable generation. I will enhance the model when a better base model arrives (like SD XL new one).

  • This is a Checkpoint dataset.

  • I recommend you to follow me on my instagram account, where I will explain about AI image generation: https://www.instagram.com/eddiemauro.design/

Intro

PRODUCT DESIGN (minimalism-eddiemauro) CHECKPOINT: Hi, I‚Äôm a product and car designer, and I‚Äôm so excited to test with AI, I think is a good tool for designing. This tool is so useful for the design process (shapes-ideas generation), but more than that, it helps so much to refine aesthetically. Also, you can turn sketch and 3D schemes into render style.

ORIGINAL MODEL: eddiemauro 1.5. Express the minimalism concept. Matte finishing.

VARIANT MODEL: eddiemauro 1.5b. The prompt is more precise, and it adapts better with objects, but minimalism style is less. The object shape is more realistic, so I consider the original model is more "creative". Also, is less matte. (also known as eddiemauro3.5).

VARIANT MODEL v.2: eddiemauro 2. The prompt is more precise, and it adapts better with objects than original and first variant mode, but the minimalism style is less. The object shape is more realistic, so I consider the original model is more "creative". It is more matte when you apply hires.fix and img2img mode. It is more colorful, and It tends to have sometimes weird color combinations.

VARIANT MODEL v.2.5: eddiemauro 2.5. The prompt is more precise, and it adapts better to objects than the previous one, and the consistence of objects shapes is so good. It has a perfect balance between consistency and creativity. It works better with low Steps and CFG because was trained with 768 dimension. Furthermore, it is less colorful, a less saturated than the previous models, but this can be solved by increasing CFG. If you want to access this model soon, please be part of my lv.1 membership on Ko-fi:

If you want to support my work and help me to upload more models (with better quality), you can do it by entering here and donating, I would greatly appreciate it: https://ko-fi.com/eddiemauro

Installation

  • I use Automatic1111, the best UI for Stable Diffusion image generation, so I recommend you to install locally or use it online with some Colab or other hosting. You can find online instructions or videos to do that. If you are going to install locally, you can watch this tutorial online and I recommend you to have at least a 6-8 Gb of VRAM Graphic Card (nvidia) to have a stable interface and launch with ‚ÄúMicrosoft Edge‚Äù because you will have problems on ‚ÄúGoogle Chrome‚Äù. Try also to install ‚Äúmedvram‚Äù or ‚Äúlowvram‚Äù options besides ‚Äúxformers‚Äù (search online how to).

  • You have to install the Checkpoint model to use.

  • Please for image creation you have to follow all my recommendations, if you don't, it is impossible to generate a good image quality. Also, you have to consider that from today AI image generation is not so consistent and perfect, you have to invest time to get it and make plenty of tests.

Recommendations for image generation

  • Activation token/caption: Inside prompt space, the first word has to be: ‚Äú3D product render‚Äù, ‚Äúproduct render‚Äù or "3D product render style" to activate the style. It is mandatory, if you don't do it, it will not work properly.

  • Another recommended prompting: Inside prompt you can use those words that will enhance the image generation: in the positive space, ‚Äúfuturistic, finely detailed, purism, ue 5, a computer rendering, minimalism, octane render, 4k‚Äù; in the negative space: ‚Äú(worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale)), cropped, text, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, duplicate, blurry, semi-realistic, out of frame, ugly, deformed‚Äù. You can also watch the image metadata of example images here and simulate the prompt.

  • Textual inversion/embedding or Lora tool recommended: I consider that ‚ÄúEasyNegative‚Äù is one best of textual inversion for negative prompt space, you should use it. Download here and install it, putting the file inside ‚Äúembeddings‚Äù. You can use it also ‚ÄúDetail Tweaker‚Äù to even reduce the details of the image, for that, you have to download from here, install like a Lora and use it inside positive prompt with a value of ‚Äú-0.5‚Äù. Use it when you realize the checkpoint used has so many details, but not when you see that minimalism is on it. This can change the shape of objects considerably. You can use another Lora's like "Epi noiseoffset" or "Godard Style", but not any of my Lora's of product design minimalism.

  • VAE: Mostly it is recommended to use the ‚Äúvae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned‚Äù Stable Diffusion standard.

  • Clip Skip: It was trained on 2, so use 2.

  • Steps and CFG: It is recommended to use Steps from ‚Äú20-40‚Äù and CFG scale from ‚Äú6-9‚Äù, the ideal is: steps 30, CFG 8. For next models, those values could change.

  • Color adjustment: When you feel there is a color extra in the image, just put it in Negative prompt: "weird colors", or the color you intend to avoid. The v.2 tends to be so colorful.

  • Sampler: I use mostly ‚ÄúEulerA‚Äù, ‚ÄúDPM++SDE Karras‚Äù or ‚ÄúDPM++2S a‚Äù. Euler tends to be simpler and more creative. Make experimentation with other samplers if you like.

  • Batch: In txt2img try to put a value of 4 to generate more than 1 image and watch the generations. If you have a good graphic card, you can use ‚ÄúBatch size‚Äù, this will create at same time 4 images, increasing generation time; but if your computer cannot handle this, change to ‚ÄúBatch count‚Äù that will create 4 images in a row (not a same time), but generation time will be more.

  • Image aspect: Try to use these dimensions: 512x512, 768x512, 512x768, but even you can experiment with different. Don't generate bigger images because the style could be lost, if you want to create a bigger image, use hires.fix in txt2img mode, img2img increase method or Ultimate SD Upscale script extension + ControlNet, or just upscaling with GAN models.

  • Create bigger images: There are 4 different methods to create large images in Stable Diffusion, you can check online how to. For first method ‚Äútxt2img hires.fix‚Äù, I recommend you to use upscale model called ‚Äú4x-UltraSharp‚Äù, downloading here just ‚Äú.pth‚Äù file, and then installing it, putting inside ‚ÄúESRGAN‚Äù file. In hires.fix option put any ‚Äúupscale by‚Äù value, and then with a ‚Äúdenoise strength‚Äù of ‚Äú0.5-0.7‚Äù. For the second method, you have to select first the image generated in txt2img and then putting in img2img mode, increasing dimension at least ‚Äú1,5 times‚Äù with a ‚Äúdenoise strength‚Äù from ‚Äú0.3-0.5‚Äù. For the third method, you can use the same configuration of img2img, but activating ‚Äútile‚Äù mode of ‚ÄúControlNet‚Äù extension and also the script of ‚ÄúUltimate SD Upscale‚Äù, but for that, I recommend you to watch a tutorial here. For the last method, you have to pass the generated image in txt2img to ‚Äúextras‚Äù and then select a GAN model and scale it, you can also use the ‚Äú4x-UltraSharp‚Äù model.

  • Get more control of your creation: Use ‚ÄúControlNet‚Äù extension to generate a more controlled shape of what you want, and even you can test it with sketches. Use ‚ÄúScribble‚Äù or ‚ÄúLineart‚Äù modes. For that, I recommend you to install this extension and then learn to how to use. There are plenty of online videos about it.

  • Copy prompt for image metadata: You can download my example images here and put it inside ‚ÄúPNG info‚Äù tab from Automatic1111

Example Prompting:

Positive prompt:¬†

3D product render, futuristic armchair, finely detailed, purism, ue 5, a computer rendering, minimalism, octane render, 4k

Negative prompt:¬†

EasyNegative, (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale)), cropped, text, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, duplicate, blurry, semi-realistic, out of frame, ugly, deformed

Steps: from 20-40 (For EulerA is enough 20, DPM++SDE Karras or DPM++2S a)

CFG scale: 6-9 (8 Ideal).

What comes for the future

I‚Äôm already trying to enhance the model. This was trained with 512 image aspect, so I will try with 768 (bigger one), and also other configurations (like changing captions, steps, epochs, etc.). If you like a better model of this version, try to keep supporting me on ko-fi, if there are more people supporting me, I can invest more time to train and enhance models, but if this doesn't happen I cannot.¬†

I launched my first private model for my Ko-fi membership lv.1, called "eddiemauro scene" minimalistic scenery creation for rendering. If you want to access to private models, you can support me and subscribe to this membership. I will also start to upload here more models centered on product and car design.


License

Watch here a Stable Diffusion license link. In the case of this specific model, use it for whatever you want in terms of image generation, also commercial (sell images you generate). It is prohibited:

  • Upload this model to any server or public online site without my permission.

  • Share online this model without my permission, using my exact model with a different name or uploading this model and then run it on services that generate images for money.

  • Merge it with a checkpoint or a Lora, and then publish it or share online, just talk to me first. In the future,

  • Sell this model or merges using this model.


Supporting

You can follow me on my social networks. I will show my process and also design tips and tools. Also, you can check my webpage and in case of you need a design service, I work like a freelance.

http://eddiemauro.design/

https://www.facebook.com/eddiemauro.design

https://www.instagram.com/eddiemauro.design

https://www.linkedin.com/in/eddiemauro

https://www.behance.net/eadesign1

items.name: AnyLoRA - Checkpoint
items.description:
AnyLoRA

Add a ‚ù§Ô∏è to receive future updates.
Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon üÖøÔ∏è or feel free to buy me a coffee ‚òï

Available on the following websites with GPU acceleration:

  • Sinkin.ai

Remember to use the pruned version when training (less vram needed).
Also this is mostly for training on anime, drawings and cartoon.

I made this model to ensure my future LoRA training is compatible with newer models, plus to get a model with a style neutral enough to get accurate styles with any style LoRA. Training on this model is much more effective conpared to NAI, so at the end you might want to adjust the weight or offset (I suspect that's because NAI is now much diluted in newer models). I usually find good results at 0.65 weigth that I later offset to 1.

This is good for inference (again, especially with styles) even if I made it mainly for training. It ended up being super good for generating pics and it's now my go-to anime model. It also eats very little vram.

The first version I'm uploading is a fp16-pruned with no baked vae, which is less than 2 GB, meaning you can get up to 6 epochs in the same batch on a colab.

Just make sure you use CLIP skip 2 and booru style tags when training.

Remember to use a good vae when generating, or images wil look desaturated. I suggest WD Vae or FT MSE. Or you can use the baked vae version.
